{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781111662122,"sessionID":"ses_14d8dece1ffed2LpK29diLpPvm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_mq4x75qt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"README.md","content":"b'# Temperature Converter CLI\\n\\nA command-line tool for converting temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin.\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\nEnsure Python 3 is installed. The tool can be run directly from the `converters.py` module.\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\nThe tool provides the following commands:\\n\\n- `celsius_to_fahrenheit <value>`: Convert Celsius to Fahrenheit.\\n- `fahrenheit_to_celsius <value>`: Convert Fahrenheit to Celsius.\\n- `celsius_to_kelvin <value>`: Convert Celsius to Kelvin.\\n\\n## Examples\\n\\n```bash\\n$ python converters.py celsius_to_fahrenheit 0\\n32.0\\n\\n$ python converters.py fahrenheit_to_celsius 212\\n100.0\\n\\n$ python converters.py celsius_to_kelvin -273.15\\n0.0\\n```\\n\\n## Error Handling\\n\\nThe tool validates inputs:\\n- Non-numeric values (e.g., strings, `None`) raise `TypeError: Input must be a number`.\\n- Boolean values (e.g., `True`, `False`) raise `TypeError: Booleans are not valid temperature values`.\\n\\n## Testing\\n\\nRun unit tests with `pytest`:\\n\\n```bash\\n$ pytest test_converters.py\\n```'"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws/README.md","time":{"start":1781111662109,"end":1781111662121}},"id":"prt_eb287260f001J2wULO4NKX38Jn","sessionID":"ses_14d8dece1ffed2LpK29diLpPvm","messageID":"msg_eb283aa0d001doCfTQ42SjIxrd"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781111662233,"sessionID":"ses_14d8dece1ffed2LpK29diLpPvm","part":{"id":"prt_eb2872695001GAHiDpdVZZdIuc","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"96855423e47d0bd2921e4abd993f0bced30bbd35","messageID":"msg_eb283aa0d001doCfTQ42SjIxrd","sessionID":"ses_14d8dece1ffed2LpK29diLpPvm","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"input":0,"output":0,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781111662648,"sessionID":"ses_14d8dece1ffed2LpK29diLpPvm","part":{"id":"prt_eb287283600185AsAvM43fevGS","messageID":"msg_eb28726d3001WWqrFcXMNxL1ER","sessionID":"ses_14d8dece1ffed2LpK29diLpPvm","snapshot":"96855423e47d0bd2921e4abd993f0bced30bbd35","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781112341464,"sessionID":"ses_14d8dece1ffed2LpK29diLpPvm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_8iw9mfa7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws/cli.py","content":"b'#!/usr/bin/env python3\\n# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\\n\\nimport argparse\\nfrom converters import celsius_to_fahrenheit, fahrenheit_to_celsius, celsius_to_kelvin\\n\\ndef main():\\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Temperature Converter CLI\")\\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\\n\\n    # Celsius to Fahrenheit\\n    c2f_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"celsius_to_fahrenheit\", help=\"Convert Celsius to Fahrenheit\")\\n    c2f_parser.add_argument(\"value\", type=float, help=\"Temperature in Celsius\")\\n\\n    # Fahrenheit to Celsius\\n    f2c_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"fahrenheit_to_celsius\", help=\"Convert Fahrenheit to Celsius\")\\n    f2c_parser.add_argument(\"value\", type=float, help=\"Temperature in Fahrenheit\")\\n\\n    # Celsius to Kelvin\\n    c2k_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"celsius_to_kelvin\", help=\"Convert Celsius to Kelvin\")\\n    c2k_parser.add_argument(\"value\", type=float, help=\"Temperature in Celsius\")\\n\\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n\\n    try:\\n        if args.command == \"celsius_to_fahrenheit\":\\n            result = celsius_to_fahrenheit(args.value)\\n        elif args.command == \"fahrenheit_to_celsius\":\\n            result = fahrenheit_to_celsius(args.value)\\n        elif args.command == \"celsius_to_kelvin\":\\n            result = celsius_to_kelvin(args.value)\\n        else:\\n            parser.error(\"Unknown command\")\\n        print(f\"{result:.1f}\")\\n    except Exception as e:\\n        print(f\"Error: {e}\")\\n\\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\\n    main()'"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws/cli.py","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws/cli.py","time":{"start":1781112341450,"end":1781112341462}},"id":"prt_eb29183b4001z22QVDVx64ZCeQ","sessionID":"ses_14d8dece1ffed2LpK29diLpPvm","messageID":"msg_eb28726d3001WWqrFcXMNxL1ER"}}
